Download and install:
  jython 2.5.3 [http://search.maven.org/remotecontent?filepath=org/python/jython-installer/2.5.3/jython-installer-2.5.3.jar]
  virtualenv 1.8.2 [https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/v/virtualenv/virtualenv-1.8.2.tar.gz]

After that create your virtual enviroment:
  $ virtualenv -p /path/to/jython venv

Start using new enviroment, type:
  $ source venv/bin/activate

Install django and django-jython:
  (venv) $ pip install https://www.djangoproject.com/download/1.2.7/tarball/
  (venv) $ pip install django-jython

Edit file runserver.sh and set right path to virtualenv.

You can now execute the script:
  $ bash runserver.sh

And browse the serverweb to http://localhost:8000

Enjoy.
